/* Windows resource script — embeds the app icon into the exe so
 * Windows Explorer / taskbar / Alt-Tab show it without needing the
 * BMP file at runtime.
 *
 * Numeric id 1 is the convention for "the app's primary icon":
 * Explorer scans the .exe, finds the lowest-numbered ICON resource,
 * and uses it as the file icon. SDL2 does NOT use this; it uses the
 * runtime SDL_SetWindowIcon path instead (see render_init). Both
 * exist for redundancy: the .ico covers pre-run state (file manager,
 * shortcuts), the runtime BMP covers the live window. */
1 ICON "miroiptv.ico"
